File descriptions:

lab4c_tcp.c: Source file for lab4c_tcp. The executable connects to the server with an address and a port, using TCP, then sends/receives info for the temperature sensor over a socket

lab4c_tls.c: Source file for lab4c_tls. The executable connects to the server with an address and a port. This time, the server is authenticated using openSSL library and connection is encrypted.

Makefile: default: compiles source files into lab4c_tcp executables
	clean: deletes all programs and output created by the Makefile and restore the directory to its freshly untarred state
	dist: creates the deliverable tarball

README: Contains description of files, resources used and additional comments regarding the project

Resources used:

http://fm4dd.com/openssl/sslconnect.htm
https://www.tutorialspoint.com/unix_sockets/socket_client_example.htm
https://www.openssl.org/docs/manmaster/man7/ssl.html